<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="J" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Joan" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Joan,</orth> 1) female noun prop.: a) of J. la Pucelle or J. of Arc: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.101" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 3</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.3" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 6, 3</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 49</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 2</bibl> b) of a hawk: <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 1, 4</bibl>.<lb />2) designation of a peasant girl: <cit><quote>some men must love my lady and some J.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 3.207" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 207</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>groan for J.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.182" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 182</bibl></cit> (Q<hi rend="sub">1</hi> <emph>love</emph>). <cit><quote>while greasy J. doth keel the pot,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.930" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 930</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.930" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 930</bibl> <cit><quote>Alice madam, or J. madam?</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.112" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 2, 112.</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>now can I make any J. a lady,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.184" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 184</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>